 and she said no tank tops, spaghetti straps, absolutely no denim and no T-shirts. And when asked for clarification she said, nothing that you're falling out of. So I thought, 'I'm not falling out of these shorts.'\" \nStoel rage-tweeted a considerable amount, noting she felt the supposed rule was arbitrary and anti-feminist. \n\nGood dress code rules: no gang attire, no explicit imagery, no pajamas...Bad dress code rules: no female shoulders, legs, bra straps...\n\u2014 Sylva (@queenfeminist) July 28, 2015\n\nJC Penney told Mashable in an email, however, that the dress code isn't discriminatory at all:\nJCPenney's dress code policy for store associates prohibits wearing shorts of any length.  New store associates who join the company are given a copy of the dress code policy and are required to sign an acknowledgment form as part of their on boarding process . This policy applies to both male and female associates at every store.\nRegardless of whether or not JC Penney was in the wrong on this one, Stoel is currently looking for employment elsewhere.\n      window._msla=window.loadScriptAsync||function(src,id){if(document.getElementById(id))return;var js=document.createElement('script');js.id=id;js.src=src;document.getElementsByTagName('script')[0].parentNode.insertBefore(js,fjs);};\n_msla(\"//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\",\"twitter_jssdk\");","mainEntityOfPage":"True","metadata":{"page":1,"omnitureData":{"channel":"watercooler","content_type":"article","v_buy":null,"v_buy_i":null,"h_pub":29.5,"h_buy":null,"h_pub_buy":null,"v_cur":3.5,"v_max":3.6,"v_cur_i":3,"v_max_i":3,"events":"event52,event61,event62","top_channel":"watercooler","content_source_type":"Internal","content_source_name":"Internal","author_name":"Lindsey Robertson","age":"1","pub_day":31,"pub_month":7,"pub_year":2015,"pub_date":"07/31/2015","sourced_from":"Internal","isPostView":true,"post_lead_type":"Default","topics":"Conversations,dress code,JC Penney,shorts,Uncategorized,Watercooler","campaig